Rating: 3
Reduced sugar to 1/2 cup. Used zest of one lemon and juice of two. Kids didn't care for nuts in the crust, so I'd make it without nuts next time. Froze extra crust mixture in a freezer bag. Used 2-inch foil cups instead of making squares (removing the paper insert). Sprayed bottom of cups with Pam. Be sure to tamp down the crust - I used the bottom of a glass ramekin, dusting with flour each time. Poured filling into cups using a funnel. Made very pretty and portable dessert.

