Rating: 3
Added ground almonds instead of hazelnuts to crust and baked it for 25 min. Increased filling 2.5 times but decreased sugar to 1/2 cup per recipe requirement. Added 1/4 cup flour to filling to thicken it. The entire cake was wonderful but the crust was the best. I will use it for my cheesecake recipes from now on.

Rating: 4
I just made this recipe and it's excellent!! I got just the right amount of piquantness after reading the other reviews and then added my own extras to that. I took the advice of one contributor and doubled the filling - excellent idea. So, I used 1/3cup of lemon juice, plus 2 tlbs., and two tlbs. of lemon zest. Be sure to tamp down the crust well before baking. One contributor found the filling texture a bit odd. I think it has something to do with using the processor to mix it. I suggest beating with a wire whisk - not as inclined to become frothy and light. Also, I added 1/3 cup flour to the filling to give it body. Don't look any further - just tweek this to your own taste. BTW, I love this site and I enjoy all you comments. Very helpful. Thank you.

