Rating: 4
So easy to make and delicious. I was glad to have reduced the sugar on the filling to only 1/2 cup, otherwise, this would have come out too sweet for my taste. I also ended up doubling the lemon juice cause I prefer it tart. Instead of sifting powdered sugar, I spread some apricot glaze on top giving it a nice rusty gloss and keeping it moist even after being put in the fridge(c/o Francois Payard's lemon tart recipe). Bec of ease in preparation and the same tart-taste gratification, I prefer to make this over lemon tart now.

